The penetration efficiency of CPPs into BY-2 suspension cells and young true leaves of N. benthamiana, A. thaliana, Moneymaker tomato, O. sativa Nipponbare, and poplar, and O. sativa callus was determined using confocal laser scanning microscopy (CLSM, ZeissLSM 700, Carl Zeiss, Oberkochen, Germany). The intracellular localization of TAMRA-labeled CPP was observed using excitation at 555 nm for the detection of TAMRA fluorescence. The total number of cells was counted using differential interfering contrast images. The efficiency was determined as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
